{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17638503","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17638503"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:54:56+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:54:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17714"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17714","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17714"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10428"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72121"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10428","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10428"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17714"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57591"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"5586"},{"type":"tags","id":"10419"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24347"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24363"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72121","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72121"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ELight entering the eye must be focused precisely on the retina for clear vision. This focusing power is achieved through multiple refractive surfaces.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the relative contribution of the eye\u0027s optical components to total refractive power?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Lens provides most power with minimal corneal contribution","Cornea and lens contribute equally","Cornea provides one-third and lens provides two-thirds","Aqueous humour provides the majority of refractive power","Cornea provides two-thirds and lens provides one-third"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecornea provides approximately two-thirds of the eye\u0027s total refractive power\u003C/strong\u003E, while the \u003Cstrong\u003Elens contributes the remaining one-third\u003C/strong\u003E. This distribution occurs because the difference in refractive index between air and the cornea is much greater than between the internal components of the eye.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Elens provides most power with minimal corneal contribution\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as it reverses the actual relationship between corneal and lens refractive power.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecornea and lens contribute equally\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as the cornea\u0027s contribution is significantly larger than the lens.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecornea provides one-third and lens provides two-thirds\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as it reverses the actual proportions of refractive power.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eaqueous humour provides the majority of refractive power\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as the aqueous humour has minimal refractive effect due to its similar refractive index to surrounding structures.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe cornea\u0027s greater refractive power is due to the large change in refractive index as light moves from air (n=1.0) to corneal tissue (n=1.376). While the lens can change shape to adjust focus for near vision, its basic refractive power is less than the cornea\u0027s.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Light rays are bent (refracted) when passing through media of different densities, with greater bending occurring at greater differences in refractive index.","The cornea provides about two-thirds of the eye\u0027s total refractive power due to the large difference in refractive index between air and corneal tissue.","The lens provides the remaining one-third of refractive power and can change shape to fine-tune focusing."],"references":["Hall JE, Hall ME. Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology. 14th ed. Philadelphia, PA: Elsevier; 2020.","Tortora, G. J., Mellifont, R., Derrickson, B., Burkett, B., Peoples, G., D, D. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, Asia-Pacific Edition,  2nd Edition. John Wiley \u0026 Sons Australia; 2019."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57591"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17714"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57591","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57591"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-20T22:46:53+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-20T22:47:32+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10428"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72121"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags",